1948: Yasuda Bank is renamed the Fuji Bank, Limited.
1950: The Nippon Kangyo Bank and IBJ are privatized.
1971: The Dai-ichi Bank and the Nippon Kangyo Bank merge to form the Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank, Limited.
