Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. Announces Consolidated Earnings Results for the Full Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jul 9 17
Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. announced consolidated earnings results for the full year ended March 31, 2017. For the year, the company reported total revenue was 2,877,062 million against 3,384,065 million a year ago. Income before income tax expense was ¥480,375 million against ¥1,196,605 million a year ago. Net income attributable to company shareholders was ¥362,440 million or ¥14.28 diluted per share against ¥850,492 million or ¥33.50 diluted per share a year ago. Cash flows from operating activities were ¥1,213,308 million against ¥241,710 million a year ago. Net interest income was ¥907,318 million against ¥1,004,764 million a year ago. Income before income tax expense was ¥480,375 million against ¥1,196,605 million a year ago.


Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. Appoints Yasuhiko Hashimoto as New Executive Officer, Joint Head of Europe, Middle East and Africa
Jul 3 17
Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. has announced the appointment of Yasuhiko Hashimoto as an executive officer, joint head of Europe, Middle East and Africa, effective July 3, 2017.


Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. Approves Partial Amendment to the Articles of Incorporation
Jun 28 17
Mizuho Financial Group, Inc., at its Ordinary General Meeting of Shareholders held on June 23, 2017, has approved partial amendment to the Articles of Incorporation.








 












